    "description": "<p>Your vision shifts into a sickly yellow tint. Your muscles tense up and contract inside you, made twitchy as new sensory information floods your brain.</p><p>You gain the following benefits and powers while wearing the goblin mask:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Darkvision</strong>. You can see in dim light within 60 feet of you as if it were bright light, and in darkness as if it were dim light.</p><p></p></li><li><p><strong>Goblin Tongue</strong>. You can speak, read, and write Goblin as a language.</p><p></p></li><li><p><strong>Nimble Escape</strong>. While wearing it, you can use an action to expend 1 of its charges to take the Disengage or Hide action as a bonus action during your turn. </p></li></ul><p></p><p>This mask has 5 charges. The mask regains 1d4 + 1 charges daily at sunrise.</p><p>If you expend the maskâ€™s last charge, roll a d20. On a 1, the mask shrivels away and is destroyed.</p>",
